                            <comment id="14474385" author="melix" created="Tue, 30 Apr 2013 08:03:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is a smaller code snippet showing the problem:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;    @CompileStatic
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Object&lt;/span&gt; convertValueToType(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Object&lt;/span&gt; value, &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Class&lt;/span&gt; targetType) {
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (value &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;instanceof&lt;/span&gt; CharSequence) {
                value = value.toString()
            }
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (value &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;instanceof&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;) {
                &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; strValue = value.trim()                    
            }
    }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The generated bytecode looks like:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;00014 LTestScripttestShouldNotThrowIncompatibleArgToFunVerifyError0; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Object&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Class&lt;/span&gt; . .  :  :     ALOAD 1
00015 LTestScripttestShouldNotThrowIncompatibleArgToFunVerifyError0; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Object&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Class&lt;/span&gt; . .  : &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Object&lt;/span&gt;  :     INVOKEVIRTUAL java/lang/&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;.trim ()Ljava/lang/&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;which means that the first parameter (&lt;tt&gt;ALOAD 1&lt;/tt&gt;) is loaded but no &lt;tt&gt;CHECKCAST&lt;/tt&gt; is added to ensure the object is of the right type.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14474401" author="melix" created="Tue, 30 Apr 2013 09:57:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Updating status to blocker since the bug is more problematic than it looks: it&apos;s related to handling of flow typing within conditional branches which can lead to invalid bytecode with &lt;tt&gt;@CompileStatic&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
